{"title_page": "Cult (Apocalyptica album)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Cult\n| type       = Album\n| artist     = [[Apocalyptica (band)|Apocalyptica]]\n| cover      = Cult - Apocalyptica - cover art.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 2 October [[2000 in music|2000]]\n| recorded   = 1999 \u2013 28 April 2000\n| venue      =\n| studio     = [[Petrax Studios]], [[Hollola]]\n\n[[Horus Sound Studio]], [[Hannover]] \u2013 Vocals (Path Vol.2)\n\n[[Woodhouse Studio]], [[Hagen]] \u2013 Vocals (Hope Vol.2)\n| genre      = [[Cello metal]], [[symphonic metal]], [[neo-classical metal]], [[progressive metal]], classical\n| length     = 1:15:30 (Both Discs)\n| label      = [[Mercury Records|Mercury]]/[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n| producer   = [[Hiili Hiilesmaa|Kai \"Hiili\" Hiilesmaa]]\n| prev_title = [[Inquisition Symphony (album)|Inquisition Symphony]]\n| prev_year  = 1998\n| next_title = [[The Best of Apocalyptica]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Special Edition\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = Cult Special Edition.jpeg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = 2001's Special Edition alternate [[Album cover]]\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Cult''''' is the title of the third full-length [[LP record|LP]] by the band [[Apocalyptica (band)|Apocalyptica]] released in 2000 with a special-edition released in 2001 containing an extra disc, mixed and mastered at [[Finnvox]]. Apocalyptica's first two albums consisted mostly of [[cover versions]]; ''Cult'' was their first album to feature mainly original composition, along with using distortion effects much more boldly and frequently, which gave the album a more orchestral sound, and also the album experimented with vocals and other [[instrumentation]]. There are some versions of the first release with \"Path Vol. 2\" as the first track and \"Path\" as the fourteenth. This is the last Apocalyptica album to feature Max Lilja on cello. The song \"Hope Vol.2\" has a music video which features scenes from the film ''[[Vidocq (2001 film)|Vidocq]]''. ''Cult'' along with ''[[Inquisition Symphony (album)|Inquisition Symphony]]'' and ''[[Live (Apocalyptica album)|Live]]'' were all released together in the '''Limited Edition Collectors Box Set'''.<ref>https://www.metal-archives.com/albums/Apocalyptica/Collectors_Box_Set/184816</ref> \n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = \n| total_length    = 52:48\n\n| title1          = [[Path Vol. 1 & 2|Path]]\n| note1           = \n| writer1         = \n| length1         = 3:08\n| title2          = Struggle\n| note2           = \n| writer2         = \n| length2         = 3:26\n| title3          = Romance\n| note3           = \n| writer3         = \n| length3         = 3:28\n| title4          = Pray!\n| note4           = \n| writer4         = \n| length4         = 4:22\n| title5          = In Memoriam\n| note5           = \n| writer5         = \n| length5         = 4:41\n| title6          = Hyperventilation\n| note6           = \n| writer6         = \n| length6         = 4:28\n| title7          = Beyond Time\n| note7           = \n| writer7         = \n| length7         = 3:57\n| title8          = Hope\n| note8           = \n| writer8         = \n| length8         = 3:24\n| title9          = Kaamos\n| note9           = \n| writer9         = \n| length9         = 4:42\n| title10         = Coma\n| note10          = Live at Hollola Church\n| writer10        = \n| length10        = 6:59\n| title11         = [[In the Hall of the Mountain King|Hall of the Mountain King]]\n| note11          = [[Edvard Grieg]] [[Cover version|cover]], from ''[[Peer Gynt (Grieg)|Peer Gynt, Op. 23, Act II, Pt. 5]]''\n| length11        = 3:29\n| title12         = [[Until It Sleeps]]\n| note12          = [[Metallica]] cover, from ''[[Load (album)|Load]]''\n| length12        = 3:15\n| title13         = Fight Fire with Fire\n| note13          = [[Metallica]] cover, from ''[[Ride the Lightning]]